hostname
uptime
clear
ls - list
ls -la - long listing with all files
lscpu - list cpu
lspci - list pc interface
cd - change directory 
pwd - present working directory
mkdir - make directory
rmdir - remove empty directory
rm - remove files
rm -rf - remove files recursively and force
ifconfig - IP address and MAC address
adduser username = to create new user
deluser username = delete user 
sudo su - = switch to root 
sudo su - username = switch to other user 
exit =  exit from terminal 
cd .. = back 
id = to check user and group information


Relative and absolute path:


Important files 
cat /etc/passwd
cat /etc/shadow
cat /etc/groups
cat /etc/shells

root user uid 0
uid=0(root) gid=0(root) groups=0(root)


application user uid will be 1 to 999



directory structure:

/ = root 
/home = home 
/dev = devices
/etc = configuration 
/bin = binaries
/var = logs and runtime files 
/opt = application files 
/usr = Library files 


